<HEADLINE>
TAIWANESE UNIVERSITIES ATTEND INT'L EDUCATION SHOW IN SINGAPORE
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  March  6  (CNA) 03/06/07  18:58:13 (By Luis Huang)
</P>
<P>
A Taiwanese delegation comprised of personnel in charge of
international exchanges from 25 universities is currently
attending an international education show in Singapore, held
under the auspices of the Asia-Pacific  Association  for
International Education (APAIE) , an official with the Ministry
of Education said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the 25 universities' participation in
the educational exhibition, which is being held March 6-9 on the
sideline of the 2007 APAIE Conference, is aimed at attracting
more foreign students to pursue advanced studies in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, led by Vice Minister of Education Lu Mu-lin, will
take advantage of the international show to expound on recent
developments and the competitive edge of Taiwan's institutions of
higher education, as well as government measures aimed at luring
foreigners to study Mandarin in Taiwan, the official said.
</P>
<P>
While in Singapore, delegation members will also seek to step up
academic exchanges and cooperation with foreign academic
institutions and  assimilate their  experience  to  help
accelerate  the internationalization of Taiwan's higher education
institutions by taking part in a series of seminars and
presentations, the official continued.
</P>
<P>
Among the universities participating in the five-day show are
National Taiwan University, National Cheng Kung University,
National Chengchi University, National Tsinghua University and
National Chung Hsing University.
</P>
